		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
				<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">One Time Pad</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Telecomix Crypto Munitions Bureau</h3>
			<div id="contentSub">(Redirected from <a href="/w/index.php?title=OTP&amp;redirect=no" title="OTP">OTP</a>)</div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>The <b>one time pad</b> cipher is arguably one of the most simple ciphers. The cipher is completely unbreakable by means of logics. Computers can not crack it. The only known method to find the correct keys is through <i>torture</i>. As torture is one form of cryptanalysis (its called "rubber hose cryptanalysis") we could if we want say that this cipher is in fact breakable.
</p><p>Notice that remote key exchange over an unsecure network is not possible. ONLY exchange cipherkeys directly with the person you wish to communicate with.
</p><p><b>If you ever plan on using the OTP cipher, you really need to make sure that you completely understand it. It is simple to make mistakes!</b>
</p>
